        <content><![CDATA[<h1 class="title topictitle1"><span class="ng-scope"><strong>Using the NeedIt Form</strong></span></h1>
<p><span class="ng-scope"><strong>Use the NeedIt application to request services and goods from several departments.</strong></span></p>
<ul><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong> Legal</strong></span></li><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong>Human Resources</strong></span></li><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong>Facilities</strong></span></li></ul>
<h2 class="title sectiontitle"><span class="ng-scope"><strong>NeedIt Form Fields</strong></span></h2>
<ol><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong>For new NeedIt records, the <em>Requested for</em> field is pre-populated with your name.  If you are opening a NeedIt request for someone else, you can change the value in the <em>Requested for</em>  field. </strong></span></li><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong>The <em>Requested for email</em> field is automatically populated if you change the user in the <em>Requested for</em> field. You can change the <em>Requested for email</em> field value. </strong></span></li><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong>The choices in the <em>What needed</em> field depend on the value in the <em>Request type</em> field.  </strong></span></li><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong>If the value in the <em>What needed field</em> is &#39;Other&#39;, the <em>Other</em> field appears.  Use the <em>Other</em> field to add a few words about your request.   </strong></span></li><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong>Use the calendar picker in the <em>When needed</em> field to set the due date for the NeedIt request.   </strong></span></li><li><span class="ng-scope"><strong>Use the <em>Short description</em> and <em>Description</em> fields to provide more information about your request. </strong></span></li></ol>
<div class="note tm-element"><span class="notetitle">Note: <span class="ng-scope"><strong>When creating NeedIt requests, the <em>When needed</em> date cannot be today or in the past.</strong></span><br /></span></div>
<p> </p>
<div class="related-links role-embedded_help_admin tm-element">
